Ex-Federal Commissioner for Information and South-South Leader, Chief Edwin Clark, on Tuesday, endorsed the Presidential Candidate of Labour Party, LP, Peter Obi for the forthcoming poll. Clark, who addressed Journalists at his Asokoro residence, Abuja, declared that with the former Anambra governor as President of Nigeria, the country would be more united. According to him, one who must be the next President of the country must be educated and experienced, stressing that South-East should be allowed to produce the next President of the country. He insisted that the zone has resourceful and educated people who can govern the country.